        "#### Determine the distribution of  僩糟¥n",
        "¥n",
        "**Determine the distribution of $Y = 1_(X>tau)$**, given that $X$ follows an exponential distribution with rate parameter $¥¥lambda = -ln(¥¥theta)$.¥n",
        "Identify the possible values that the random variable $Y = ¥¥mathbf{1}_{(X>¥¥tau)}$ can take. The r.v $Y = ¥¥mathbf{1}_{(X>¥¥tau)}$ is an indicator function, that takes a value of 1 if the condition is true, otherwise 0. $Y = 1$ if $X > ¥¥tau$ ; $Y = 0$ if $X ¥¥le ¥¥tau$. $Y$ follows a discrete distribution.¥n",
        "¥n",
        "**Calculate the probability $P(Y=1)$.**¥n",
        "- For an exponential distribution with rate parameter $¥¥lambda$, the probability $P(X > x)$ (also known as the survival function) is given by $P(X > x) = e^{-¥¥lambda x}$. $X$ follows an exponential distribution with rate parameter $¥¥lambda = -¥¥ln¥¥theta$. Therefore, substituting $x = ¥¥tau$ $P(Y=1) = P(X > ¥¥tau) = e^{-¥¥lambda ¥¥tau}$, $¥¥quad$ $P(Y=1) = e^{-(-¥¥ln¥¥theta) ¥¥tau}$¥n",
        "¥n",
        "¥n",
        "**Express $P(Y=1)$ in terms of $¥¥theta$ and $¥¥tau$**.¥n",
        "- We have $P(Y=1) = e^{-(-¥¥ln¥¥theta) ¥¥tau}$. Simplify the exponent $P(Y=1) = e^{(¥¥ln¥¥theta) ¥¥tau}$. Using the logarithm property $e^{a ¥¥ln b} = b^a$, we can rewrite this as $P(Y=1) = e^{¥¥ln(¥¥theta^¥¥tau)}$. $P(Y=1) = ¥¥theta^¥¥tau$$¥n",
        "¥n",
        "Let $p = ¥¥theta^¥¥tau$. Since $0 < ¥¥theta < 1$ and $¥¥tau > 0$ (as $X > ¥¥tau$ implies $¥¥tau$ must be positive for the indicator to be meaningful in this context), it follows that $0 < p < 1$.¥n",
        "¥n",
        "Since $Y$ can only take values 0 or 1, and we have determined the probability $P(Y=1) = p$, it means $P(Y=1) = ¥¥theta^¥¥tau$, $¥¥quad$ $P(Y=0) = 1 - P(Y=1) = 1 - ¥¥theta^¥¥tau$¥n",
        "¥n",
        "This is the definition of a **Bernoulli distribution**. Therefore, $Y$ follows a Bernoulli distribution with parameter $p = ¥¥theta^¥¥tau$.¥n",
        "¥n",
        "**Distribution of Y** $Y ¥¥sim ¥¥text{Bernoulli}(¥¥theta^¥¥tau)$¥n",
        "¥n",
        "**The expectation of Yi, E[Yi], in terms of theta and tau.** $Y_i ¥¥sim ¥¥text{Bernoulli}(p)$ where $p = ¥¥tau ¥¥cdot ¥¥theta^{X_i}$. For a Bernoulli r.v. $Y$ with probability $p$, its expectation $E[Y]$ is given by $E[Y] = p$. Express E[Y_i] in terms of theta and tau: $E[Y_i] = ¥¥tau ¥¥cdot ¥¥theta^{X_i}$"
      ]
